
1. Clone our training project https://github.com/plrdev/TrainingApp
2. Setup development environment https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup
3. Choose between React Native CLI (Recommended) or Expo (no native code changes)

4. Remember setup steps for both Android and iOS (Mac users)
5. Remember to install dependencies (npm install) and iOS install pods (npx pod-install) or (cd ios & pod install)
6. Run the training app (npm run ios & npm run android) ‚úÖ

# Bonus: Change the text displayed to something, for example ‚ÄúGofore React Native training is awesome!‚Äù üôå

# Bonus: Get the app running also on your own device (not just simulator / emulator)
Tip: https://reactnative.dev/docs/running-on-device

# Bonus: Initialize and run your own project from scratch 
Tip: (npx react-native init <ProjectName>) 
Tip 2: Add "--template react-native-template-typescript" for a typescript project 
